      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Alpine White over Cinnamon Nappa leather. This example features the legendary S54B32 inline-six, delivering 333 hp through six individual throttle bodies and a crisp Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission. Mechanically, this vehicle is impeccable: the subframe has been proactively reinforced, rod bearings replaced, and the dual-VANOS system fully overhauled with Beisan components. It retains its factory limited-slip differential and M-tuned suspension, offering telepathic handling and a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The paint depth is consistent across all panels, and the chassis remains remarkably clean. A true driver's specimen maintained to an exacting standard.",
